  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving multi-purpose cash assistance to vulnerable communities in Kasai, Kasai Central, Kasai Oriental, Ituri and Tanganyika. This WFP project provides cash assistance to 77,320 people, including 21,000 women, 20,000 men, and over 36,000 children. This project is part of an $80 million CERF allocation to support cash programming in response to increasing food insecurity in 6 countries.</narrative>
  </description>
